---
const effectiveDate = '2025-12-31';
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>Privacy Policy - Libre Fasting</title>
		<meta
			name="description"
			content="Privacy policy for the Libre Fasting app. Learn what data is collected, how it is used, and your choices."
		/>
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
		<link
			href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@600;800&family=Inter:wght@400;600&display=swap"
			rel="stylesheet"
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<main class="page">
			<header class="hero">
				<nav class="nav">
					<a class="nav-link" href="/">← Back to Libre By Design</a>
				</nav>
				<h1 class="title">Privacy Policy</h1>
				<p class="subtitle">Libre Fasting</p>
				<p class="meta">Effective date: {effectiveDate}</p>
				<p class="meta-link">
					Self-link:
					<a href="https://librebydesign.com/privacy">https://librebydesign.com/privacy</a>
				</p>
			</header>

			<section class="card">
				<p class="lead">
					Libre Fasting (&quot;we,&quot; &quot;our,&quot; or &quot;us&quot;) respects your
					privacy. This policy explains what data the app collects, how it is used, and
					the choices you have.
				</p>

				<div class="section">
					<h2>Definitions</h2>
					<p>
						&quot;Collect&quot; refers to transmitting data off the device in a way that allows
						you and/or your third-party partners to access it for a period longer than
						necessary to service the transmitted request in real time.
					</p>
					<p>
						&quot;Third-party partners&quot; include analytics tools, advertising networks,
						third-party SDKs, or other external vendors whose code you have added to the app.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="section">
					<h2>Data We Collect</h2>
					<p>
						Libre Fasting does not collect any data as defined above. The app stores the
						following information only on your device:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Fasting data you enter (fast type, start and end times, duration, and completion details).</li>
						<li>Optional metrics you enter (weight and body fat).</li>
						<li>App settings (quick fast preference, theme and color choices, notification toggle).</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="section">
					<h2>How We Use Data</h2>
					<p>We use your data solely to provide the app's features, including:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Tracking your fasting sessions and progress.</li>
						<li>Showing your history and completion stats.</li>
						<li>Scheduling reminders if you enable notifications.</li>
						<li>Exporting your history when you choose to share it.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="section">
					<h2>Data Storage and Sharing</h2>
					<ul>
						<li>All data is stored locally on your device.</li>
						<li>We do not collect, transmit, store, or sell your data on any server.</li>
						<li>We do not use analytics, advertising, or tracking SDKs.</li>
						<li>We do not share your data with third-party partners.</li>
						<li>If you export your history, you choose where it goes using your device's share options.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="section">
					<h2>Notifications</h2>
					<p>
						If you enable reminders, the app schedules local notifications on your device. We
						do not send push notifications or collect device tokens. You can turn reminders off
						at any time in Settings.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="section">
					<h2>Data Retention</h2>
					<p>
						Your data remains on your device until you delete it in the app or uninstall the
						app, which removes locally stored data.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="section">
					<h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
					<p>
						Libre Fasting is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect
						personal information from children.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="section">
					<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
					<p>We may update this policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted here with a revised effective date.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="section">
					<h2>Contact</h2>
					<p>
						If you have questions about this policy, contact us at
						<span class="contact">hi [at] librebydesign [dot] com</span>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>

		<style>
			:root {
				--bg-deep: #0a0a0a;
				--bg-glow: #11151b;
				--card: rgba(22, 25, 30, 0.9);
				--border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
				--text-primary: #f7f7f7;
				--text-secondary: #a5adba;
				--accent: #ffd93d;
			}

			* {
				box-sizing: border-box;
				margin: 0;
				padding: 0;
			}

			body {
				min-height: 100vh;
				font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
				color: var(--text-primary);
				background:
					radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(78, 205, 196, 0.18), transparent 55%),
					radial-gradient(circle at 12% 20%, rgba(255, 217, 61, 0.14), transparent 45%),
					linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-deep), var(--bg-glow));
				line-height: 1.7;
			}

			.page {
				max-width: 980px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem 4rem;
			}

			.hero {
				padding: 1rem 0 2.5rem;
				text-align: left;
				animation: rise 0.8s ease forwards;
			}

			.nav {
				margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
			}

			.nav-link {
				color: var(--text-secondary);
				text-decoration: none;
				font-weight: 600;
				font-size: 0.95rem;
				transition: color 0.2s ease;
			}

			.nav-link:hover {
				color: var(--text-primary);
			}

			.title {
				font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
				font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
				font-weight: 800;
				letter-spacing: -0.02em;
				margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
			}

			.subtitle {
				font-size: 1.2rem;
				color: var(--text-secondary);
				margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
			}

			.meta {
				font-size: 0.95rem;
				color: var(--accent);
				font-weight: 600;
			}

			.meta-link {
				margin-top: 0.4rem;
				font-size: 0.9rem;
				color: var(--text-secondary);
			}

			.meta-link a {
				color: var(--text-primary);
				text-decoration: none;
			}

			.meta-link a:hover {
				text-decoration: underline;
			}

			.card {
				background: var(--card);
				border: 1px solid var(--border);
				border-radius: 20px;
				padding: 2.5rem;
				box-shadow: 0 20px 45px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
				animation: fadeIn 1s ease forwards;
			}

			.lead {
				font-size: 1.05rem;
				color: var(--text-secondary);
				margin-bottom: 2rem;
			}

			.section {
				margin-bottom: 2rem;
			}

			.section:last-child {
				margin-bottom: 0;
			}

			h2 {
				font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
				font-size: 1.35rem;
				margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
				color: var(--text-primary);
			}

			p {
				color: var(--text-secondary);
				margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
			}

			ul {
				list-style: none;
				padding-left: 0;
				color: var(--text-secondary);
			}

			li {
				margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
				padding-left: 1.4rem;
				position: relative;
			}

			li::before {
				content: '•';
				position: absolute;
				left: 0;
				color: var(--accent);
				font-weight: 700;
			}

			.contact {
				color: var(--text-primary);
				font-weight: 600;
			}

			@keyframes fadeIn {
				from {
					opacity: 0;
					transform: translateY(12px);
				}
				to {
					opacity: 1;
					transform: translateY(0);
				}
			}

			@keyframes rise {
				from {
					opacity: 0;
					transform: translateY(6px);
				}
				to {
					opacity: 1;
					transform: translateY(0);
				}
			}

			@media (max-width: 640px) {
				.page {
					padding: 2rem 1rem 3rem;
				}

				.card {
					padding: 1.75rem;
				}

				.nav {
					margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
				}
			}
		</style>
	</body>
</html>
